---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Standards | LaTech Editorial Publishing"
  description="Our commitment to quality, accuracy, and rigorous review processes for all published content."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Editorial Standards</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="narrow-content">
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          LaTech Editorial Publishing maintains the highest standards of editorial excellence. All content published on our platform undergoes rigorous review to ensure accuracy, clarity, and intellectual contribution. We are committed to editorial independence and make decisions based solely on quality, rigor, and relevance.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Review Process</h2>
        <h3>Scholarly Content</h3>
        <p>
          All scholarly articles undergo peer review by independent experts in the relevant field. Reviewers evaluate submissions based on:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Methodological rigor and validity</li>
          <li>Originality and contribution to knowledge</li>
          <li>Clarity and quality of writing</li>
          <li>Appropriate use of sources and citations</li>
          <li>Ethical considerations</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Editorial Content</h3>
        <p>
          Editorial content is reviewed for accuracy, quality, and relevance. While editorial pieces may express opinions, they must be grounded in evidence and rigorous analysis. All factual claims are verified before publication.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Citation Standards</h2>
        <p>
          All published content must properly attribute sources and provide citations where appropriate. We require:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Proper attribution for all ideas, data, and quotations from other sources</li>
          <li>Links to sources where possible and appropriate</li>
          <li>Clear distinction between original analysis and cited material</li>
          <li>Consistent citation style appropriate to the content type</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Corrections Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We are committed to accuracy and transparency. When errors are identified:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Corrections will be made promptly upon verification</li>
          <li>Significant corrections will be noted at the top of the article</li>
          <li>Major corrections may be announced separately</li>
          <li>Correction history will be maintained for transparency</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you identify an error in our content, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> with details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Conflicts of Interest</h2>
        <p>
          We maintain strict policies regarding conflicts of interest:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Authors must disclose any potential conflicts of interest</li>
          <li>Editors recuse themselves from reviewing content where conflicts exist</li>
          <li>Financial relationships, institutional affiliations, and personal relationships that could influence content are disclosed</li>
          <li>Editorial decisions are made independently of commercial, political, or institutional pressures</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Fact-Checking</h2>
        <p>
          All published content undergoes fact-checking to verify:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Accuracy of factual claims</li>
          <li>Proper interpretation of data and statistics</li>
          <li>Correct attribution of quotes and sources</li>
          <li>Verification of links and references</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Sources are documented and available for review. We prioritize primary sources and peer-reviewed research when available.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .page-header h1 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  .page-content {
    padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0;
  }
  
  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }
  
  .content-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }
  
  .content-section h3 {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
  
  .content-section ul {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
  }
  
  .content-section li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
</style>
